sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Mobile App (Client)
    participant Server as Auth Server
    Note over App: App stores the shared secret in Keystore (Android) / Keychain (iOS).
    Note over App, Server: Shared secret is known by both sides but is never exchanged


    App->>App: 1. Generate UUID (Device ID) on first launch
    App->>App: 2. Create timestamp
    App->>App: 3. Compute hash(Device ID + timestamp + secret)

    App->>Server: HTTP request (headers: X-Device-Id, X-Timestamp, X-Signature)

    Note over Server: 4. Validate timestamp (replay protection)
    Note over Server: 5. Compute hash(Device ID + timestamp + secret) on server side

    alt Hash comparison successful
        Server-->>App: 200 OK (access granted) access_token
    else Invalid hash or expired
        Server-->>App: 403 Forbidden (access denied)
    end
